Thus, under the following conditions, the votes contained in one or more electoral packages may be partially counted The results in the minutes do not match; the minutes on the counting and calculation of votes are not in the file or are not in the possession of the chairman of the electoral committee or there are obvious errors or amendments in the minutes.
In addition, the total counting of the fully completed ballot papers can take place if there is a difference between the alleged winner and the second-placed winner equal to or less than one percent, provided that at the beginning of the session there is an express request from the party or coalition chairman, who is the second of the aforementioned candidates.
Vote counting may also take place in its entirety if, after completion of the ordinary calculation, it is established that the difference between the alleged winner and the candidate in second place is equal to or less than one percent, provided that there is an explicit request from a representative of the party whose candidate has become second, in which case the electoral packages that have been subjected to a partial counting would be excluded.
