Colom guarantees Portillo's extradition to the United States
Guatemala’s President, <0xC3><0x81>lvaro Colom, announced on Tuesday that he would consent to the extradition of former governor Alfonso Portillo so that he would be responsible in the United States for the $70 million money laundering conspiracy.
Thus, the trial of the U.S. request for extradition of Portillo ends so that it can be brought to justice there.
