At 3:30 p.m., police approached Montral No. 35 after receiving a call from a neighbor who had watched four people attempt to enter the building.
The four were immediately arrested.
Park or mountain?
Apart from the disputes about the fees, the architects agree with the tender.
The urban tender for the 16 gates reopens the debate on the importance of Collserola in Barcelona.
In the mid-1980s, at the height of the now-disappearing Corporación Metropolitana de Barcelona (CMB), this administration published its libel about the promotion of Collserola.
The brochure described the mountain as a huge park in Barcelona city.
He was even compared in numbers to Central Park of New York.
With the fall of the CMB in 1987, the park became the upper limit of Barcelona in the eyes of many, because the capital of Catalonia is one of the few that does not spread in the north-south direction, but up (mountains) and down (sea).
The classification of Collserolas as a natural park plays with this idea.
As an example, it was no longer Central Park, but Yellowstone with wild boars in the role of yogis.
This was the case when the city issued a huge tender in September, consisting of 16 competitions, for further gates to Collserola.
Without a doubt, a gate points to the concept of a park.
Either that's the case, or someone is planning to set gates to the countryside.
The question arises of itself: Collserola, park or mountain?
The invitation to tender is the topic of discussion for all Barcelona architects, not only from an organisational point of view, but also with a view to reflecting on the city.
It is almost a recurring theme that two members of this old caste, who meet in the elevator, can draw on.
And this fact provides the material for one of the rare similarities between what three architects from Barcelona think about it and some university professors who applied for the project.
Miguel Roldán, Daniel Modol and Marta Bayona: The tender is appropriate.
For Roldán, it is "necessary" to speak of the "front on the mountain" after the attack on the coast, insofar as the discourse of Ildefons Cerda, about the green apples, has not been carried out.
“You should start with the principle that Barcelona’s largest park is the beach.
Among other things, because it is easily accessible.
Collserola is more complex", the architect considers, for which the title "Gates of Collserola" carries a "lexical trap": it is not to be "imagined as access to a park, but as a delimitation of areas on which to act."
Modol, like Roldán and Bayona with urban planning experience, considers the proposal to be an "intellectual challenge" that carries "some dangers".
Dangers arising from the "uncertainty that the design of a public space entails today" following the experiences from the 1980s, which had their "swan song" in the area of the forum.
The first fear is one's own limitation on what may be cultivated.
"Limiting something always means determining the next step", i.e. exceeding it.
"You have to think about new urban planning tools, because the current [referring to the Plan General Metropolitano (PGM)] can lead to a real disaster."
Modol, who holds closer to the question, says simplified, the side of Collserola, which goes towards Vallesana, "can be understood as a park that does not go towards Barcelona", for purely topographical reasons.
Modol recalls that there is already a study by the Patronat de Collserola, which should not "be stumbled upon deaf ears", although he is grateful to the city council for giving its body the opportunity to participate in this project "from the first moment".
He also notes that the proximity of the mountain to the city is the guiding letter that allows architects to participate in the debate, although he expresses his "doubts" about whether this technical profile should lead the multidisciplinary teams established ("just the right thing," he says) "We architects should only be a tool."
Bayona suggests that the answer to the question in the headline of this article is complex, as in the tender conditions a global view of Collserola is missing: "There were 16 competitions advertised in cross-section," he says, "on the axis mountain-sea. But there is no longitudinal perspective that looks at the area in its entirety."
At least in his case, this led him to take part in the 16 competitions.
Otherwise, the program and the definition of a project for a gate would collide with that of the architect of the gate next to it.
In his opinion, the city should absolutely guarantee that the strip directly above the Ronda de Dalt is equipped in its entire length to create a soft transition between the city and green areas.
Casino awards Jonás Larrazábal who comes free
After 72 days of silence, the representative of Casino Red freed the brother of the Mayor of Monterrey from the trial being held against him for alleged blackmail.
After 72 days of imprisonment, Manuel Jonás Larrazábal is released after the representative of Casino Red has granted him a pardon before the Second Criminal Court of the District leading the trial against the brother of the Mayor of Monterrey for extortion.
After the assassination of Casino Royale, Sergio Gil García, the owner of Casino Red, published a series of photos and videos showing Manuel Jonás, who allegedly forced him to pay a sum of money so that the city council would approve the secret operation of the betting house.
