At the same time, it is necessary to mitigate the scarcity of fossil resources in order to continue producing electricity consistently, without forgetting the imperative need to reduce greenhouse gas emissions, a topic that has disappeared from the ecological debate, in order to fight climate irregularities.
The Fukushima accident does not change any of these parameters.
Therefore, Germany remains isolated in its decision to refrain from nuclear power.
